<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbaad3f76-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397m–5"><num value="1397m–5">§ 1397m–5.</num><heading> Rule of construction</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this division shall be construed as—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbaad3f77-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397m–5/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> limiting any cause of action or other relief related to obligations under this division that is available under the law of any State, or political subdivision thereof; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbaad3f78-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397m–5/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> creating a private cause of action for a violation of this division.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbaad3f79-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531">Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531</ref>, title XX, § 2046, as added <ref href="/us/pl/111/148/tVI/s6703/a/1/C">Pub. L. 111–148, title VI, § 6703(a)(1)(C)</ref>, <date date="2010-03-23">Mar. 23, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/798">124 Stat. 798</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
